{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Reform statutory leave so all workers have enough paid leave to truly live",
        "additional_details": "Workers currently are entitled to only 5.6 weeks paid leave including bank holidays, while school children have around 13 weeks off each year.\r\nWe feel this imbalance reduces life satisfaction, limits time for family, hobbies, and personal growth.\r\nLife is for living, not just working. Paid leave laws should reflect that reality.\r\nFlexible leave for wellbeing could allow people to recharge, care for family, and pursue meaningful life experiences, creating happier, healthier and productive communities.",
        "background": "I want the Government to reform statutory annual leave so that all workers:\r\n \r\nReceive roughly the same number of paid holidays as school children (~13 weeks per year). Have flexible leave options for personal projects, mental health, and family commitments.",
